\n<\n[1]>This place is the \c[18]Hole\c[0],\. huh?\.\. It doesn't look too different from up there...
\n<\n[1]>As always,\. humans overreact to anything a bit wild...\.\.\. \BST[1,Neneko2]I bet this whole "Hole" deal is just a fluke~

<
[1]>I'll get 
[2] back and go back home...\.\.\. I've already lost too much time on this!
\n<???>Move yer feet lads,\. we've been called back!
\n<Dwarf Soldier I>I'm tired o' running after those damn ugly snouts!
\n<Dwarf Soldier I>Lead' should just order us t' raid 'em!\.\. It'd end in a day!
\n<Dwarf Soldier II>Shush yer trap,\. ye ain't seen their nest did ya?
\n<Dwarf Soldier II>That place 's a hell!\.\. Keep movin' now,\. or Lady \c[18]Ruina\c[0] will kick us out!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Those shorties...\.\.\. the \c[18]dwarves\c[0] live around here,\. huh?\.\. I remember stories about 'em.
\n<\n[1]>Hmph...\.\.\. They look annoying,\. but if they're bossing this place around...
\n<\n[1]>Maybe their "lead" knows something about my targets?
\n<\n[1]>Those soldiers headed there,\. to the East...\.\.\. their place should be close...
\n<\n[1]>Or should I go West and do things my way...?

"\fs[\v[320]]\fn<\v[319]>Any aggression against our proud race will stain your \c[18]Reputation\c[0] with our Faction.\fn<GameFont>\fs[30]"

\n<Dwarf Axeman>The Fortress 's past this portal.\.\. Mind yer manners inside.
\n<Dwarf Axeman>Th' Rumbling Pike is past this point.\.\. Can't let anyone pass.\.\. 'Tis too dangerous,\. lady.
\n<Dwarf Axeman>Hmph...\.\.\. very well then missie...\.\.\. I guess ye hav' yer permit,\. huh.
\n<Dwarf Axeman>Rumbling Pike is past this point,\. missie...\.\.\. watch yer surroundings...
\n<Dwarf Lookout>One wrong step,\. catgirl,\. and I'll crank it up!
A familiar face welcomes you.\.\. Her childlike appearance hasn't changed since the first time you met.
\n<\n[1]>HOW DID YOU GET HERE BEFORE ME?!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>I went through hell,\. so why are you so relaxed!?
\n<Lina>Now now Nene,\. don't be mad at me.\.\. Remember?\.\. \BST[1]As a proud Dwarven Engineer,\. I can come and go between here and the Surface freely!
\n<Lina>My boss is the leader around here,\. and I go wherever \C[18]Ruina\C[0] commands me to~
Neneko's fur lowers again,\. the sunny attitude of the young dwarf is effective...\.\.\. and useful.
\n<\n[1]>Your boss,\. huh?\.\. I'm looking for something here so it could be useful...\.\.\. \BST[7]But considering what happened last time I went asking for help...
\n<\n[1]>And...\.\.\. huh...\.\.\. can I meet her?\.\. I...\.\.\. I'll behave...
\n<Lina>Oh,\. I don't know about that Nene...\.\.\. she's so busy with all's happening around here that...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Tch...\.\.\. alright,\. I get it.\.\. I won't get you involved...\.\.\. \BST[8]Just tell me where to find her,\. I'll deal with it myself.\.\. Alone.
The frown on Neneko's face doesn't shake the dwarf,\. well aware about who her boss is.
\n<Lina>Oh,\. don't be like that,\. I can't exactly put in a good word with my boss,\. I'm not important enough in the Fortress.
\n<Lina>But I can talk with the guards,\. they are good dwarves!\.\. \BST[4]I'm sure they won't attack you if I ask them nicely~
\n<Lina>And the legendary constructor will give you audience if you keep being this cute and behave well around her dwarves!
\n<Lina>Just head East from here,\. this is the "usual" way to go if you came from the Surface!
\n<\n[1]>Hmph...\.\.\. yeah,\. sure,\. I'll do just that.\.\. \BST[1]Now, don't you have "pipes" to maintain or something?
The frontal assault has failed,\. Neneko now barely looks at the short redhead,\. and glances around while she speaks.
\n<Lina>I'll head inside now,\. the Fortress is always bustling with life and I've got a lot of work to do!
\n<Lina>Make sure to come and find me!\.\. I'll be at the \c[18]Mining District\c[0]!\.\. You'll like it~
\n<\n[1]>Wait...\.\.\. that unbearably high pitched whining...\.\.\. Anzu!\.\.
Neneko turns towards the commotion just as Anzu gives a scream of horror.\.\
\n<\n[5]>Nooooooooo!!!!\.\. My dress!!\.\. This was my favorite outdoor wear,\. you horrid thing!!\.\.
Anzu was covering herself up,\. the entire top half of her outfit ripped to shreds,\. exposing her pale,\. pink skin...\.\.\. and completely bare breasts.\.\.
She was surrounded by large,\. lizardlike beasts...\.\.\. but they didn't seem entirely interested in her.\.\. More curious or anything than hostile.\.\.
Really,\. if Neneko had to describe them,\. they looked...\.\.\. dopey.\.\.
The only one that stood out was the one closest to Anzu,\. which had red dripping from its large maw.\.\.
With tears in her eyes Anzu grabbed at the red,\. which,\. rather than blood,\. was clearly the tattered remains of her dress.\.\.
The beast exhaled,\. not opening its mouth even a bit for Anzu to retrieve her pride or outfit.\.\. Her hair was blown back from the steam.\.\.
With her composure AND decency lost,\. Anzu turned tail and began running,\. concealing her breasts and wailing the whole time.\.\.
The one that had 'attacked' Anzu continued loitering,\. not even acknowledging the cloth still in its maw.\.\.
